
[1]inventory

   IN'VENTORY, n.

   1. An account, catalogue or schedule of all the goods and chattels of a
   deceased person. In some of the United States,the inventory must
   include an account of the real as well as the personal estate of the
   deceased.

   2. A catalogue of movables.

   3. A catalogue of account of particular things. [An indefinite use of
   the word.]

   IN'VENTORY, v.t. To make an inventory of; to make a list, catalogue or
     schedule of; as, to inventory the goods and estate of the deceased.

   1. To insert or register in an account of goods.
